data.description: Discover this spacious townhome inside the beltway! Ownership form is a Condominium although the home is a Townhome. A rare find, this 3-bedroom Mill Stream townhome offers an inviting ambiance with a well-designed open floor plan. The main level boasts a spacious living room with a dining area, enhanced by hardwood flooring throughout, and a deck to enjoy the outdoors. The well-appointed eat-in kitchen provides ample cabinet and counter space.  Upstairs, the primary bedroom awaits with vaulted ceilings and skylights, a full-wall closet, and an en-suite bath. Two additional bedrooms and a shared full bath complete the upper level. The walkout lower level includes a family room with an additional full bath and laundry room, featuring a cozy wood-burning fireplace. The private fenced patio creates a delightful retreat, providing a restful space and room for kids to play. There is also access to an attached 1-car garage and driveway parking.  The condo fee covers exterior maintenance, encompassing the roof, siding, fencing, front steps, and railing. Recent updates include a roof replacement in 2021, new windows in 2018, and new HVAC in 2014.  This residence is mere minutes from shopping, dining, Van Dorn Metro, public transportation, and major commuter routes. The upcoming West End development, situated less than half a mile away from the old Landmark Mall location, promises to introduce additional retail, restaurants, and entertainment options. Nestled inside the beltway, this home ensures effortless access to the Pentagon, Mark Center, Fort Belvoir, Crystal City, and Washington DC. Residents enjoy the convenience of a nearby Metro Bus Stop at the community's edge, while Van Dorn Metro is just a few minutes away, ensuring seamless connectivity for commuters.
